Merge pull request #77 from swapnilmj/patch-2

Fixed a typo in link
Fixed rpm spec to remove changelog from documentation

Final preparations for releasing 1.5.0

* Removing python API artifacts. Will be done properly right after releasing 1.5.0

Doc stuff fixes in preparation for releasing 1.5.0

Revert "Final preparations for releasing 1.5.0"

This reverts commit b27ddfd1d13e869a72c77bb0e514f4887c945122.
Added debian packaing script + more fixes to RPM creation + fixed error message text
Fixed utf-8 with BOM issues and reinstated the matching test + docs stuff
Added python API message to README

Multiple queries on CLI + Reuse of loaded data + Full code refactoring (full python API) + RPM compiles q to binary

Included changes:
pick 8b4342d Refactored q to expose objects, and added a python package wrapper
pick b0d28b1 Internalized exception handling into the q main object
pick faf3904 Added reuse of loaded data + stdin injection to module API + tests
pick 08cf2bb Allow different input params for each loaded file + loading file manually + fixed modeling of query encoding + tests
pick 3a7fffd Separation of populate phases
pick 92d0bb6 Provide table structure as part of responses + merge _populate method versions
pick d04a24c Multiple queries on CLI + load data from string API + finer details in table structure response + tests
pick d90c392 modified non existent file error msg + fixed response bug in table_structure when there are errors
pick 5908a75 Fixed bug in str of the response
pick a9dcc74 New RPM creation which matches commit hash to version, and compiles q
pick 90fd18a Fixed permissions for new RPM.

Fixed a typo in link

Fixed typo accidentally caused while fixing another typo.

Merge pull request #75 from Fil/patch-1

typo

Added full control of input/output quoting of data + tests

Supported quoting types are none, miminal, non numeric and all
Fixed proper encoding when opening file, limiting zipping from stdin

Fixed csv double quote escaping behavior. New behavior is as in csv standards.

Added tests to match

Quoting output properly will be done separately
Support for SELECT statements without a table, allowing things such as SELECT 5+8 and such

Merge pull request #35 from mattn/windows_bat

Add q.bat

Lots of changes preparing version 1.3.0b (beta). See below

- Added column type inference, still needs to be tested
- Added column name detection when using -H
- Added a test suite, in preparation for full refactoring
- Added parsing mode flag - strict, relaxed of fluffy (a.k.a old behavior mode)
- Breaking change - Changed -H behavior so it's now a flag an not a parameter (1 line always)
- Fixed tab delimition parameter problem
- Some more better error reporting
- Removed engine v1, including engine parameter. Support for mult-char delimiters has been removed - breaking change
Added gitter chatroom access for feedback
